            . I am the wife of Thomas Porter, he is a <rs id="t18280911-278-viclabel1428" type="occupation">chandler</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-278-victim1540 t18280911-278-viclabel1428"></join>, and lives in 
               <persName id="t18280911-278-person1542">Baldwin's-gardens</persName>
            . On the 14th of July I lost a hock of bacon, it was found in the bed-room in the workhouse.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-278-person1543">
                  MARY 
                  ANN LEWIS
               <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1543" type="surname" value="ANN LEWIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1543" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1543" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with my father in the prosecutor's house - I was standing at the door when the prisoner went out with a piece of bacon under her arm; I did not know but that she had bought it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-278-person1544">
                  CHARLES 
                  CARTER
               <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1544" type="surname" value="CARTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1544" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1544" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am porter of the gate at St. Andrew's work-house - the prisoner was nurse of one of the wards; she went out on the 14th of July; I let her in, and in a few minutes the prosecutor came and asked to speak to her; I sent for her and the master - they asked about taking the bacon, she strongly denied it; the master sent me to search the ward, and I found it in the bed-room under the bed - the prosecutor swore to it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-278-person1545">
                  WILLIAM 
                  KIRBY
               <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1545" type="surname" value="KIRBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1545" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1545" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I received the bacon and the prisoner at the work-house; I kept it as long as I could, and then gave it up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-278-person1546">
                  CHARLOTTE 
                  PORTER
               <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1546" type="surname" value="PORTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1546" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1546" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . It was my property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The gentlewoman is very wrong; she swore it had never been cut - I had half a peck of beans in Leather-lane, and a man offered me the bacon for half a crown.</p>
               <p>COURT to 
               <persName id="t18280911-278-person1547">
                  WILLIAM 
                  KIRBY
               <interp inst="t18280911-278-person1547" type="surname" value="KIRBY"></interp>
